\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is at least intriguing to question whether highly coupled theories have
 fundamental constituents whose nature is so exotic that they have been
 overlooked.
 Drawing paralells with 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda\phi^{4}$
\end_inset

 theory, it is tempting to speculate that the Higgs particle of the standard
